4
00:01:48,650 --> 00:01:49,568
How are you getting along

5
00:01:49,569 --> 00:01:50,819
with Gao Ping's aunt?

6
00:01:54,329 --> 00:01:55,860
She just came not long ago.

7
00:01:56,049 --> 00:01:57,500
I guess it's okay.

8
00:01:58,409 --> 00:02:00,620
Your father keeps wanting to visit her.

9
00:02:00,849 --> 00:02:02,249
He thought
that she was Gao Ping's relative.

10
00:02:02,250 --> 00:02:03,420
She was her elder too.

11
00:02:03,970 --> 00:02:05,299
But he's afraid

12
00:02:05,489 --> 00:02:06,889
that Gao Ping might be too prideful.

13
00:02:06,890 --> 00:02:08,460
He's afraid
that he might feel embarrassed.

14
00:02:08,889 --> 00:02:10,580
He wants to ask you

15
00:02:10,970 --> 00:02:12,500
when's a good time to visit you two.

16
00:02:15,289 --> 00:02:16,859
You guys can wait a little longer, then.

17
00:02:17,210 --> 00:02:19,329
She just arrived
at our house not long ago.

18
00:02:19,330 --> 00:02:21,369
Both parties need to
get used to each other's presence.

19
00:02:21,370 --> 00:02:22,300
Hurry.

20
00:02:23,009 --> 00:02:23,769
Lend me a hand.

21
00:02:23,770 --> 00:02:24,659
You came from a long way.

22
00:02:24,729 --> 00:02:26,620
You didn't need to buy anything for us.

23
00:02:27,530 --> 00:02:28,568
Jiang bought them.

24
00:02:28,569 --> 00:02:29,819
He told me to deliver them to you all.

25
00:02:31,530 --> 00:02:32,419
Where are

26
00:02:32,490 --> 00:02:33,539
the two little brats?

27
00:02:34,210 --> 00:02:36,168
I told Aunty to trim

28
00:02:36,169 --> 00:02:37,180
Qi's bangs.

29
00:02:37,970 --> 00:02:39,180
Is no one keeping an eye on her?

30
00:02:39,490 --> 00:02:41,740
What if Aunty
does what she likes on a whim?

31
00:02:42,689 --> 00:02:44,209
I told her
that I would ignore her forever

32
00:02:44,210 --> 00:02:45,419
if she did that.

33
00:02:46,409 --> 00:02:47,939
I don't think she can be trusted.

34
00:02:48,449 --> 00:02:49,939
What about this?
I'll go and take a look.

35
00:02:50,689 --> 00:02:51,649
You can bring them back.

36
00:02:51,650 --> 00:02:52,408
Dad, I'll be leaving now.

37
00:02:52,409 --> 00:02:53,939
Where are you going?
Are you not having dinner?

38
00:02:59,330 --> 00:03:00,659
Where is Xiang Nan going?

39
00:03:01,129 --> 00:03:02,379
She's going to Aunt's hair saloon.

40
00:03:03,090 --> 00:03:03,859
She...

41
00:03:05,849 --> 00:03:07,900
She's going there
to pick up Cong and Qi.

42
00:03:18,810 --> 00:03:20,259
Why is Gao Ping absent again?

43
00:03:21,129 --> 00:03:22,809
Gao Ping has to prepare for

44
00:03:22,810 --> 00:03:24,568
the postdoctoral program.

45
00:03:24,569 --> 00:03:25,249
Just let him

46
00:03:25,250 --> 00:03:26,539
do his revisions at home.

47
00:03:36,050 --> 00:03:37,688
He has to prepare for his exam.

48
00:03:37,689 --> 00:03:39,288
It's fine for him to be absent.

49
00:03:39,289 --> 00:03:40,539
Look at how petty you are.

50
00:03:40,729 --> 00:03:41,939
Did I say anything?

51
00:03:42,409 --> 00:03:44,379
Why were you sighing, then?

52
00:03:44,729 --> 00:03:45,809
What? You expect me to smile

53
00:03:45,810 --> 00:03:47,419
when he's absent?

54
00:03:47,849 --> 00:03:49,740
But you don't need to feel dejected.

55
00:03:52,330 --> 00:03:53,220
Leave.

56
00:03:57,330 --> 00:03:58,740
Your father is such a good actor.

57
00:03:59,650 --> 00:04:01,259
I have something to tell Xiang Qian.

58
00:04:03,810 --> 00:04:04,859
Leave.

59
00:04:06,250 --> 00:04:07,300
We have something to discuss.

60
00:04:07,650 --> 00:04:08,688
Is this how you guys

61
00:04:08,689 --> 00:04:10,300
communicate now?

62
00:04:11,330 --> 00:04:11,969
He's so pretentious.

63
00:04:11,970 --> 00:04:12,780
Leave.

64
00:04:13,289 --> 00:04:14,369
You can prepare the vegetables.

65
00:04:14,370 --> 00:04:16,180
You can prepare them in the yard.

66
00:04:16,609 --> 00:04:17,728
I can prepare them

67
00:04:17,729 --> 00:04:18,619
anywhere I like.

68
00:04:18,890 --> 00:04:20,220
I'll prepare them at the back.

69
00:04:21,890 --> 00:04:23,020
You're something else, aren't you?

70
00:04:23,690 --> 00:04:24,419
Go now.

71
00:04:26,369 --> 00:04:27,940
Mom, I'll lend you a hand later.

72
00:04:28,169 --> 00:04:29,179
No need for that.

73
00:04:30,450 --> 00:04:31,419
Xiang Qian,

74
00:04:32,890 --> 00:04:34,140
have you met

75
00:04:35,169 --> 00:04:36,460
Xiang Zhong for the past few days?

76
00:04:39,450 --> 00:04:40,340
What's wrong?

77
00:04:40,530 --> 00:04:42,220
Did something major crop up again?

78
00:04:42,450 --> 00:04:43,739
Listen.

79
00:04:44,289 --> 00:04:45,859
Gu told me

80
00:04:46,010 --> 00:04:47,048
that Xiang Zhong

81
00:04:47,049 --> 00:04:49,020
is having a blurry affair
with someone else.

82
00:04:49,729 --> 00:04:50,449
What do you mean

83
00:04:50,450 --> 00:04:51,449
by a blurry affair?

84
00:04:51,450 --> 00:04:53,539
How could you believe
Gu's words blindly?

85
00:04:53,970 --> 00:04:54,689
Gu is telling us

86
00:04:54,690 --> 00:04:55,769
about this

87
00:04:55,770 --> 00:04:57,499
because he's concerned about our family.

88
00:04:57,809 --> 00:04:58,900
I'm back.

89
00:05:00,570 --> 00:05:01,299
Zhong.

90
00:05:01,369 --> 00:05:03,059
Mom, I bought you some apples.

91
00:05:06,530 --> 00:05:08,179
What's with the frown?

92
00:05:10,929 --> 00:05:11,859
You're back.

93
00:05:14,049 --> 00:05:15,260
Why are you staring at me?

94
00:05:15,330 --> 00:05:16,460
What's wrong?

95
00:05:17,609 --> 00:05:18,969
Dad is exhausted. Let's...

96
00:05:18,970 --> 00:05:19,808
Let's help Mom out in the kitchen.

97
00:05:19,809 --> 00:05:20,539
No need for that.

98
00:05:21,090 --> 00:05:22,220
You two can have a chat.

99
00:05:22,249 --> 00:05:23,220
I'll help her out.

100
00:05:27,770 --> 00:05:28,728
You saw that, right?

101
00:05:28,729 --> 00:05:29,329
I just arrived home.

102
00:05:29,330 --> 00:05:30,380
I didn't provoke him.

103
00:05:31,130 --> 00:05:32,820
What's with the long face?

104
00:05:33,130 --> 00:05:34,209
He said something

105
00:05:34,210 --> 00:05:35,248
about you

106
00:05:35,249 --> 00:05:36,449
right before you came back.

107
00:05:36,450 --> 00:05:37,460
What did he say?

108
00:05:37,849 --> 00:05:39,299
Dad told me this just now.

109
00:05:40,049 --> 00:05:41,728
He said Gu told him

110
00:05:41,729 --> 00:05:43,979
that Xiang Zhong had a blurry affair
with someone else.

111
00:05:45,609 --> 00:05:46,979
That's not true.

112
00:05:47,970 --> 00:05:48,769
I don't know anything.

113
00:05:48,770 --> 00:05:49,529
That's the only thing he said

114
00:05:49,530 --> 00:05:50,900
before you came back.

115
00:05:53,450 --> 00:05:55,460
I'm utterly speechless.

116
00:05:55,570 --> 00:05:56,288
I hate this place

117
00:05:56,289 --> 00:05:57,580
so much.

118
00:05:57,929 --> 00:05:59,129
What's wrong with them?

119
00:05:59,130 --> 00:06:00,168
Do they have nothing else to do

120
00:06:00,169 --> 00:06:02,099
but gossip about other people?

121
00:06:02,450 --> 00:06:03,649
They always jump to conclusions
based on rumors, huh?

122
00:06:03,650 --> 00:06:04,979
Can't they keep their mouth
in check for once?

123
00:06:05,249 --> 00:06:06,209
Wait, you...

124
00:06:06,210 --> 00:06:07,940
What are you saying?

125
00:06:09,330 --> 00:06:10,859
Jump to conclusions based on rumors?

126
00:06:11,369 --> 00:06:12,220
Xiang Zhong,

127
00:06:12,489 --> 00:06:14,089
do you think people would
jump to conclusions

128
00:06:14,090 --> 00:06:15,460
if you weren't involved
in any rumors in the first place?

129
00:06:15,770 --> 00:06:16,499
Tell us.

130
00:06:16,570 --> 00:06:17,288
About what?

131
00:06:17,289 --> 00:06:18,140
The person who accompanied you

132
00:06:18,409 --> 00:06:19,728
to the hospital two days ago,

133
00:06:19,729 --> 00:06:20,499
who is he?

134
00:06:20,609 --> 00:06:21,419
It was a guy.

135
00:06:25,169 --> 00:06:25,940
Tell us.

136
00:06:26,210 --> 00:06:27,168
Why aren't you concerned about

137
00:06:27,169 --> 00:06:28,580
the reason
I went to the hospital instead?

138
00:06:29,289 --> 00:06:30,059
Fine.

139
00:06:30,409 --> 00:06:31,499
I'll pay attention to you now.

140
00:06:31,809 --> 00:06:32,539
Tell me, then.

141
00:06:32,729 --> 00:06:33,900
Why did you head to the hospital?

142
00:06:35,090 --> 00:06:36,739
Fine. I'll tell you about it.

143
00:06:37,130 --> 00:06:37,689
I was

144
00:06:37,690 --> 00:06:39,769
scratched by my neighbor's cat.

145
00:06:39,770 --> 00:06:40,808
My neighbor accompanied me
to the hospital

146
00:06:40,809 --> 00:06:41,969
for a vaccine shot.

147
00:06:41,970 --> 00:06:42,969
Are you happy now?

148
00:06:42,970 --> 00:06:44,659
You were scratched by a cat?

149
00:06:45,289 --> 00:06:46,009
I can never get through to you.

150
00:06:46,010 --> 00:06:47,099
Where are you going?

151
00:06:47,809 --> 00:06:48,649
Xiang Zhong!

152
00:06:48,650 --> 00:06:49,419
Xiang Zhong!

153
00:06:49,570 --> 00:06:50,380
Xiang Zhong!

154
00:06:50,849 --> 00:06:51,689
- Zhong!
- Look at her.

155
00:06:51,690 --> 00:06:53,099
It's none of my business.

156
00:06:53,289 --> 00:06:54,168
Mom.

157
00:06:54,169 --> 00:06:55,168
How many times have I told you guys?

158
00:06:55,169 --> 00:06:56,048
I'm over 30 years old now.

159
00:06:56,049 --> 00:06:56,529
I know my limits.

160
00:06:56,530 --> 00:06:57,329
Dou's mother,

161
00:06:57,330 --> 00:06:58,689
we cannot apologize to you.

162
00:06:58,690 --> 00:07:00,220
Yesterday's dispute
hasn't been resolved yet.

163
00:07:01,369 --> 00:07:02,940
(Gao Ping: She posted the video
in the homeowners' group chat.)

164
00:07:03,049 --> 00:07:04,048
(Now, everyone is talking about it.)

165
00:07:04,049 --> 00:07:04,928
Even if I'm not divorced yet,

166
00:07:04,929 --> 00:07:06,340
can't I even have some male friends?

167
00:07:06,489 --> 00:07:07,248
Enough already.

168
00:07:07,249 --> 00:07:08,089
Don't say that in public.

169
00:07:08,090 --> 00:07:09,449
Don't you think it's embarrassing?

170
00:07:09,450 --> 00:07:10,449
That's right.
I'm going to say this in public.

171
00:07:10,450 --> 00:07:11,368
All of you, listen up!

172
00:07:11,369 --> 00:07:12,248
Mind your own business!

173
00:07:12,249 --> 00:07:13,969
(Dou's Mom's messages)
Stay out of other people's business!

174
00:07:13,970 --> 00:07:15,380
(This kid has propensity for violence obviously)
You can think whatever you like!

175
00:07:15,450 --> 00:07:16,460
Where are you going?

176
00:07:16,609 --> 00:07:17,529
That's none of your business!

177
00:07:17,530 --> 00:07:18,780
Aren't you going to have dinner with us?

178
00:07:19,570 --> 00:07:20,460
Look at her.

179
00:07:20,929 --> 00:07:22,260
- Listen...
- Dad.

180
00:07:22,409 --> 00:07:23,368
Can you tell Gu

181
00:07:23,369 --> 00:07:24,569
this?

182
00:07:24,570 --> 00:07:25,649
Tell him to go about with his life

183
00:07:25,650 --> 00:07:27,569
instead of meddling
with our family affairs.

184
00:07:27,570 --> 00:07:29,449
Xiang Zhong is over 30 years old now.

185
00:07:29,450 --> 00:07:30,529
Do you have to go so far as to find out

186
00:07:30,530 --> 00:07:32,099
who she went to the hospital with?

187
00:07:32,169 --> 00:07:34,340
You're making her upset on purpose.

188
00:07:34,530 --> 00:07:35,940
Where are you going, then?

189
00:07:36,090 --> 00:07:36,848
Mom,

190
00:07:36,849 --> 00:07:38,129
I need to handle some affairs
in the neighborhood.

191
00:07:38,130 --> 00:07:38,969
I'll pick up Cong and Qi

192
00:07:38,970 --> 00:07:39,808
and head home.

193
00:07:39,809 --> 00:07:41,340
You should leave after dinner!

194
00:07:45,609 --> 00:07:47,220
Enough. We'll have dinner together.

195
00:07:48,489 --> 00:07:49,340
I'm not having dinner.

196
00:07:49,450 --> 00:07:50,499
What's wrong?

197
00:07:50,570 --> 00:07:51,580
I'm not having dinner.

198
00:07:51,849 --> 00:07:53,009
Where are you going?

199
00:07:53,010 --> 00:07:53,859
I don't know.

200
00:07:55,970 --> 00:07:56,659
Fine.

201
00:07:56,690 --> 00:07:57,529
Lanzhi, listen up!

202
00:07:57,530 --> 00:07:58,220
You...

203
00:07:58,409 --> 00:08:00,179
You better don't come back if you leave!

204
00:08:02,210 --> 00:08:03,659
Will you stop or not?

205
00:08:27,770 --> 00:08:28,659
Ms. Ma,

206
00:08:28,729 --> 00:08:29,449
I wish to retrieve

207
00:08:29,450 --> 00:08:32,089
the camera footage
on Wednesday afternoon...

208
00:08:32,090 --> 00:08:32,848
Yeah. Wednesday afternoon.

209
00:08:32,849 --> 00:08:34,139
I wish to retrieve

210
00:08:34,330 --> 00:08:35,248
the camera footage

211
00:08:35,249 --> 00:08:37,619
near the sandbox
located in the central garden.

212
00:08:37,889 --> 00:08:38,728
I'm sorry.

213
00:08:38,729 --> 00:08:40,899
The surveillance camera footage
cannot be retrieved without permission.

214
00:08:42,450 --> 00:08:43,409
I'm one of the homeowners.

215
00:08:43,410 --> 00:08:44,859
Why can't I retrieve it?

216
00:08:44,930 --> 00:08:45,809
There are rules we have to follow.

217
00:08:45,810 --> 00:08:47,248
It's not like every house owner

218
00:08:47,249 --> 00:08:48,528
can retrieve the camera footage
when they feel like it.

219
00:08:48,529 --> 00:08:49,569
We have to consider

220
00:08:49,570 --> 00:08:51,340
the privacy of other homeowners as well.

221
00:08:52,769 --> 00:08:53,409
You can't expect me to ask

222
00:08:53,410 --> 00:08:55,259
the other homeowners
for their permission, right?

223
00:08:55,450 --> 00:08:57,008
At least you have to obtain

224
00:08:57,009 --> 00:08:58,779
more than half of their permission.

225
00:08:59,330 --> 00:09:00,768
You can also use legal means

226
00:09:00,769 --> 00:09:01,809
to involve the police.

227
00:09:01,810 --> 00:09:03,619
We'll definitely give you
our full cooperation.

228
00:09:05,290 --> 00:09:06,060
Fine.

229
00:09:10,290 --> 00:09:12,379
(Greetings, fellow homeowners.)

230
00:09:12,649 --> 00:09:13,608
(I'm the mother of the child)

231
00:09:13,609 --> 00:09:16,049
(who refused to apologize
to the other mother)

232
